ues that were prompted by these anniversaries. Offering an astounding collection of materials, Remembering and Forgetting in Acadie is also accompanied by a website (www.rememberingacadie.concordia.ca) that provides access to films, audio clips, and photographs assembled on Rudin's journey through public memory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCollective memoryzMaritime Provinces. 0aPublic historyzMaritime Provinces. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Pre-Confederation (to 1867).2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144268897140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442688971423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442688971.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK